INSTALLATION
============

1) ENVIRONMENT SETUP:

  To set up the PESTO environment variable in bash: 
    export PESTO=</path/to/your/pesto/directory/>
  
  Then add PESTO to your path:
    export PATH=$PATH:$PESTO/bin
  
  If it does not already exist, create a Matlab startup file:
    mkdir -p ~/Documents/MATLAB
    vi ~/Documents/MATLAB/startup.m
  
  and append these lines to the startup.m file:
    % PESTO:
    if isempty( getenv( 'PESTO' ) ) 
    	display('Please set the PESTO environment variable' );
    else
    	addpath( [getenv( 'PESTO' ) , 'src/matlab'] );
    end
  

2) JAVA SETUP:

  If you plan on using Java adaptors, then you will need to add the following
  to your CLASSPATH environment variable:

    export CLASSPATH=$CLASSPATH:$PESTO/src/Java


3) TEST INSTALLATION: 

  Refer to the PESTO README file to see how to test the installation.

